title: Child Abuse Prevention Services in San Francisco
description: Contains information on child abuse prevention services provided by multiple departments within the City and County of San Francisco, including services run directly by City departments and programs provided by contracted organizations. Information was collected by the Controller’s Office as a first step in creating a county-wide abuse prevention plan, and includes program descriptions, cost information (where available), and categorizations by service area, protective factor, target audience, and level of prevention. This data was originally collected in FY19 for programs run during FY18. For more information please see the Controller's report at http://openbook.sfgov.org/webreports/details3.aspx?id=2778

columns.name: Program or Contract Name
columns.description: Name of program or service, from contract if applicable.

columns.name: Contractor Name
columns.description: Name of contractor for program, if applicable

columns.name: Combined Program and Contractor Name
columns.description: Combined program and contractor name. This field uniquely identifies the programs on the list.

columns.name: Program Description
columns.description: Short description of program activities and target audience

columns.name: Lead Department
columns.description: Main department responsible for program. Usually department responsible for administering the contract.

columns.name: Department Division
columns.description: A subdivision of the Lead Department, if applicable.

columns.name: Targets of Service
columns.description: Population at home the service is targeted. Children; Parents; Professionals; System

columns.name: Service Categories
columns.description: A list of one or more topical areas the program relates to. Individual service category designations are also included in the dataset in columns starting "SC"

columns.name: Levels of Prevention
columns.description: A list of one or more designations of level of prevention of the program. Individual designations are also included in the dataset in columns starting "Level". Possible values are Primary, Secondary, and Tertiary. For more detail on level of prevention see full report

columns.name: Name of Evidence Based Practice used
columns.description: Where relevant, a list of one or more California Evidence-Based Clearinghouse practices used in the program. For more information visit: https://www.cebc4cw.org/

columns.name: CEBC Rating
columns.description: Rating for the highest rated practice from the California Evidence-Based Clearinghouse used in the program. 1 is the highest rating, down to 5. NR is for programs not able to be rated. For more information visit: https://www.cebc4cw.org/ratings/scientific-rating-scale/

columns.name: CEBC Topic Areas
columns.description: A list of one or more topic areas related to any practices from the California Evidence-Based Clearinghouse used in the program. Individual topic area designations are also included in the dataset in columns starting "CEBC". For more information visit: https://www.cebc4cw.org/registry/topic-areas/

columns.name: CEBC Child Welfare Relevance
columns.description: Rating for the highest relevance practice from the California Evidence-Based Clearinghouse used in the program. Possible values are High, Medium, Low, and rating not included. For more information visit: https://www.cebc4cw.org/ratings/child-welfare-relevance-levels/

columns.name: Protective Factors
columns.description: A list of one or more protective factors addressed by the program. Individual protective factor designations are also included in the dataset in columns starting "PF".

columns.name: Name of Family First Practice
columns.description: Where relevant, a list of one or more Family First Prevention Services Act practices used in the program. For more information visit: https://preventionservices.abtsites.com/

columns.name: Family First Practice Rating
columns.description: Ratings for any Family First Prevention Services Act practices used in the program. Possible values are Well-supported, Supported, Promising, and Does not currently meet criteria. For more information visit: https://preventionservices.abtsites.com/review-process/psr

columns.name: Contracted or Direct Service
columns.description: Denotes whether a program is delivered directly by City staff (Direct Service) or through a contracted organization.

columns.name: Program Cost
columns.description: Where available, the cost, in US dollars, of the program for the Fiscal Year 2018 (July 2017-June 2018). Any deviations from this are noted in the column "What program cost represents".

columns.name: Program Cost Notes
columns.description: Notes on time period or other information about "Program Cost".

columns.name: Number of Participants
columns.description: Where available, information on the number and make up of program participants.

columns.name: Participant Number Notes
columns.description: Further notes on information in "Number of Participants".

columns.name: Contract ID Number
columns.description: Contract identification numbers for contracted programs. Multiple numbers may exist if the same program was delivered by a single contractor under two contracts over the course of Fiscal Year 2018. In those cases, the contract numbers are separated by a semicolon. Numbers are Financial System Project (F$P) Identifiers.

columns.name: Program Relevance Rating
columns.description: A rating of how targeted to child abuse prevention the program is between 1 (least targeted) and 3 (most targeted). For more detail see the Controller's report

columns.name: Audience Relevance Rating
columns.description: A rating of how relevant to child abuse prevention the target audience of the program is between 1 (least targeted) and 3 (most targeted). For more detail see the Controller's report.

columns.name: Target Children
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets children.

columns.name: Target Parents
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program Targets parents and families.

columns.name: Target Providers
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets providers and professionals.

columns.name: Target System
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the system or administrators.

columns.name: Level Primary
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program includes primary prevention activities, defined as activities that seek to raise the the awareness of the general public, business leaders, educators, service providers, and decision-makers about the scope and problems associated with child maltreatment and, the conditions that might contribute to the issue.

columns.name: Level Secondary
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program includes secondary prevention activities, defined as services and resources targeted to parents and youth at risk for child abuse or neglect. Services seek to prevent child abuse or neglect from occurring by building protective factors, which are conditions or attributes in individuals, families and communities that mitigate or eliminate risk.

columns.name: Level Tertiary
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program includes tertiary prevention activities, defined as those that focus on families where maltreatment has already occurred and seek to reduce the negative consequences of the maltreatment and to prevent its recurrence. These services provide supports and resources to children and families involved in the child welfare system to prevent re-entry and recurrence.

columns.name: PF Social-Emotional
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the protective factor social and emotional competence of children. Defined as family and child interactions that help children develop the ability to communicate clearly, recognize and regulate their emotions, and establish and maintain relationships.

columns.name: PF Parental Resilience
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the protective factor parental resilience. Defined as managing stress and functioning well when faced with challenges, adversity, and trauma.

columns.name: PF Knowledge of Parenting
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the protective factor knowledge of parenting and child development. Defined as Understanding child development and parenting strategies that support physical, cognitive, language, social, and emotional development.

columns.name: PF Concrete Support
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the protective factor concrete support in times of need. Defined as access to concrete support and services that address a family’s needs and help minimize stress caused by challenges.

columns.name: PF Social Connections
columns.description: An indicator 0 is 'No', 1 is 'Yes' of whether the program targets the protective factor social connections. Defined as positive relationships that provide emotional, informational, instrumental, and spiritual support.

whom_it_may_interest: Social workers, policy makers, child welfare researchers, public health officials, and non-profit organizations focused on child welfare and abuse prevention

queries.Monthly: SELECT lead_department, targets_of_service, service_categories, levels_of_prevention, protective_factors, date_trunc_ym('2018-01-01') AS fiscal_year, SUM(program_cost) AS total_program_cost, AVG(program_relevance_rating) AS avg_program_relevance_rating, AVG(audience_relevance_rating) AS avg_audience_relevance_rating WHERE date_trunc_ym('2018-01-01') >= start_date GROUP BY lead_department, targets_of_service, service_categories, levels_of_prevention, protective_factors ORDER BY fiscal_year
queries.Yearly: SELECT lead_department, targets_of_service, service_categories, levels_of_prevention, protective_factors, date_trunc_y('2018') AS fiscal_year, SUM(program_cost) AS total_program_cost, AVG(program_relevance_rating) AS avg_program_relevance_rating, AVG(audience_relevance_rating) AS avg_audience_relevance_rating WHERE date_trunc_y('2018') >= start_date GROUP BY lead_department, targets_of_service, service_categories, levels_of_prevention, protective_factors ORDER BY fiscal_year
